ra em alunos e se mata], ''[[Jornal do Brasil]]'' (August 7, 2001)</ref>\n|-\n| November 12, 2001\n| [[Caro, Michigan]], United States\n| Chris Buschbacher, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Chris Buschbacher, armed with a [[.22|.22-caliber]] [[rifle]] and a [[20-gauge]] [[shotgun]], took one teacher and one student hostage at the Caro Learning Center before killing himself.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/14/us/student-kills-himself-after-taking-hostages.html Student Kills Himself After Taking Hostages], ''[[New York Times]]'' (November 14, 2001)</ref>\n|-\n| December 5, 2001\n| [[Springfield, Massachusetts]], United States\n| Corey Ramos, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| At Springfield High School, a school for troubled teens, 17-year-old Corey Ramos stabs to death Reverend Theodore Brown, a counselor at the school. In 2003, Ramos is sentenced to life in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| January 15, 2002\n| [[New York City|New York]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States\n| Vincent Rodriguez, 17\n|\n| 2 injured\n| 17-year-old Vincent Rodriguez shot and wounded two students at [[Martin Luther King, Jr. High School (New York)|Martin Luther King, Jr. High School]] in [[Manhattan]], New York City, with a [[.380 ACP|.380-caliber]] [[semi-automatic pistol]]. The possible motive was that the victims had harassed Rodriguez's girlfriend.<ref>{{cite news |author= Wakin, Daniel J. |title= Gunfire Wounds 2 Students Inside a Manhattan High School |url= https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0DEED91338F935A25752C0A9649C8B63 |work= [[The New York Times]] |date= 2002-01-16 |accessdate=2008-02-20 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Baker, Al |title= Police Identify Student Wanted in School Shooting |url= https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F07E2DE1F38F93BA25752C0A9649C8B63 |work= [[The New York Times]] |date= 2002-01-18 |accessdate=2008-02-20 }}</ref> In February 2003, Rodriguez was sentenced to 10 years in prison on charges of assault and attempted assault.<ref>{